    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "OFFICERS AND DIRECTORS\nBRUCE S. GIBSON. PRESIDENT\nFIRST VICE-PRES.\nHORACE W. AMPHLETY, SE VICE PRES.\nSan Mateo Chamber of Commerce\nSAN MATEO, CALIFORNIA\nMay 24, 1921.\nDIRECTORS\nHARRY A. PECKHAM\nELIZABETH HOLE\nMANAGER\nMR.\nJOSEPH J. PHILLIPS\nRight of Way Agent\nCity Hall\nSan Francisco, Calif.\nDear Joe:\nIn answer to your letter regarding the\nestablishment\nin San Mateo of a meteorological\nobservation station at\nVarney field, would say that\nI am at present negotiating with the owners and\nlessees of Varney field and anticipate no\ndifficulty\nin returning the signed papers to you in a few days.\nSincerely yours,\nLloyd Al. Berendren."
    ],
